      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Landmark cases vividly illustrate how substantive due process safeguards freedom, such as *Griswold v. Connecticut*, which established a constitutional right to marital privacy. Furthermore, decisions like *Roe v. Wade* historically used this doctrine to protect personal autonomy regarding reproductive rights. These cases demonstrate the judiciary's role in recognizing unenumerated rights that protect individuals from unwarranted state control. These rulings solidify the idea that certain personal freedoms are inherent and protected by the Constitution.",
      "source": "target",
